Trim the @aubergine{1} and slice into thin rounds approximately 1cm thick. Halve, peel
and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the
core and seeds. Chop into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use
a #garlic press{}).

Preheat your #grill{} to high. Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #frying pan{}
on medium-high heat. Add the onion and pepper and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Cook, stirring, until soft and golden, ~{6-7%minutes}. Add the @dried oregano{1%tsp},
@tomato puree{1%tbsp}, @ground cinnamon{1/2%tsp} and half the garlic. Cook for
~{1%minute} more.

Next, stir in the @red split lentils{50%g}, @Worcester sauce{1%tbsp},
@vegetable stock paste{1%tsp} and @chopped tomatoes{1%400g can}. Add the @water{100%ml}
and @sugar{1%tsp}. Stir, bring to the boil, lower the heat to medium and simmer until
the lentils are soft (but still have a slight bite to them), ~{20-25%minutes}. If the
sauce gets too dry, just add a splash of water.

Meanwhile, lay the aubergine slices on a #baking tray{} in a single layer and drizzle
over a good glug of oil. Season with salt and pepper. Grill until browned and soft,
about ~{8-9%minutes} on each side.

> Keep an eye on them to make sure they don't burn. If they aren't soft after this
> time, just leave them under your grill for another 2-3 mins.

Remove and set aside.

== Cheat's Garlic Bread ==

In a #small bowl{}, mix the remaining garlic with the @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Cut the
@ciabatta{1} in half and smear the garlic oil over the cut side.

== Assembling the Moussaka ==

When the tomato sauce is ready, transfer the sauce to an #ovenproof dish{}. Layer over
the aubergine slices. Dollop over the @creme fraiche{75%g} and then spread it out evenly
across the top.

Sprinkle the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} over the moussaka and season with
pepper.

Grill until the cheese is golden and bubbling, about ~{5-6%minutes}. Remove from the
grill, then grill the garlic bread until golden and toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Serve the moussaka in bowls. Add a handful of @wild rocket{20%g} alongside and drizzle
with @olive oil{1/2%tsp}. Serve with the cheat's garlic bread. Enjoy!

> MOD: If you've decided to add beef mince to your meal, before you add the onion and
> pepper to your pan, add the @?British beef mince{120%g} and cook until browned,
> ~{3-4%minutes}. Break it up with a #spoon{} as it cooks. Add the onion and pepper to
> the mince and continue with the recipe as instructed.